Class PowerHashApp

  • java.lang.Object
    • PowerHashApp

  • public class PowerHashApp
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the main class that will run procedures regarding interacting with various types of hash table The user will choose which collision resolution they wish to use, the size of the table (Which will be checked by this program if it is a prime number), the data file from which input will be recieved, and the amount of random keys the user wishes to search for It has instance variables to store a hash table (which uses linear or quadratic probing) and a hash table which uses chaining It has instance variables for storing a list of all the date/time keys and an array that randomizes those keys to a specific size of an array as specified by the user
    Author:
    ShaiAarons, https://beginnersbook.com/2014/01/java-program-to-check-prime-number/ for the prime number checker
